ATSXV/AltX-listed junior and DRC Mining Week 2018 attendee Alphamin Resources Corp. (Alphamin) is looking to establish itself as one of the highest grade tin miners in the world when it starts producing metal concentrate from its US$160 million Bisie project in the Democratic Republic of Congo in H1, 2019. While the successful start-up of the mine will be a major milestone achievement for the company, it represents only the starting point for this company, who is ultimately looking to uncover and develop a wide-scale tin producing region in the country’s North Kivu province, CEO Boris Kamstra tells Laura Cornish. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 8 2018. It will be published online on the 3rd September 2018. You can read the full digital magazine here or subscribe here to receive a print copy